  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD027783",
      "title": "IDA (Iminodiacetic Acid) Generated Mesoporous Nanopolymer - A Template to Relate Surface Area, Hydrophilicity and Glycopeptides Enrichment",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Co-polymer 1,2-epoxy-5-hexene and divinyl benzene with terminal oxirane group is synthesized for the first time. High density of hydrophilic groups (-COOH, -OH) enhances hydrophilicity through facile functionalization with Diethylene Triamine (DETA) and chloroacetic acid. COOH-functionalized mesoporous polymeric beads provide high surface area and porosity, superior hydrophilicity, solvent resistance and good bio-capability for enriching N-Linked glycopeptides. Sensitivity, selectivity, reusability and batch to batch reproducibility are tested using model glycoproteins (HRP, IgG and avidin) and analyzed by MALDI-TOF-MS. Furthermore, N-glycosylation sites in N-glycopeptides of characteristic glycoproteins are identified from digested human serum.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "Orbitrap instrument was operated in positive ion mode with normalized collision energy set to 35%. All MS and MS/MS spectra were acquired in the data-dependent mode in full mass range of m/z 300 to 2000 at resolution of 60000 in FT mode. The ten most intense precursor ions were selected for MS/MS by collision-induced dissociation (CID) using a dynamic exclusion of 5 seconds, minimum relative signal intensity of 1000, and \u22652 positive charge state. Mgf files were created using Proteome Discover (version 1.4, Thermo Fisher Scientific).",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Spectra were analyzed using Mascot server against the most recent version of Uniprot human database. Variable modifications for methionine oxidation and HexNAc of asparagine, and fixed modifications of carbamidomethyl cysteines were specified, with the maximum missed cleavages of 2 and the digestion enzyme was specified as trypsin. MS mass tolerance of 10 ppm and MS/MS mass error tolerance of 0.02 Da was specified for the searches.",
      "projectTags": [],
      "keywords": [
        "Lc-ms/ms",
